Florence. Before the DUKE's palace.
DUKE
The general of our horse thou art; and we,Great in our hope, lay our best love and credenceUpon thy promising fortune.
BERTRAM
Sir, it isA charge too heavy for my strength, but yetWe'll strive to bear it for your worthy sakeTo the extreme edge of hazard.
DUKE
Then go thou forth;And fortune play upon thy prosperous helm,As thy auspicious mistress!
BERTRAM
This very day,Great Mars, I put myself into thy file:Make me but like my thoughts, and I shall proveA lover of thy drum, hater of love.
